usb-modeswitch: Fix building with newer gcc versions

In older C standards an empty parameter list implied
a function can take any number of arguments. Newer gcc
versions however are stricter about function prototypes.

Signed-off-by: Alexandru Costache <alexandru@balena.io>
Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [oe-specific]

